    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/1258</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-19">January 19,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received January 19—7:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>514. From Pell. Following conference at Foreign Office, Commission was organized
                    formally at meeting held January 18. Rules of organization and procedure were
                    adopted. Foreign Office ready to drop proposed technical committee provided
                    governments concur. All members agree that Commission is adequate. Consensus is
                    that Commission should take broad view of functions and make recommendations to
                    governments on means of enforcement, including choice of tribunals. Refer to
                    Embassy’s 8504, December 6 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>] and your 8229 December
                        30.<note n="11" xml:id="d819fn11">
                        <ref target="frus1943v01#pg_432">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 432</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1943v01#pg_435">435</ref>, respectively.</note> Request
                    authorization that Mr. Preuss<note n="12" xml:id="d819fn12">Lawrence Preuss,
                        divisional assistant (legal) in the Division of International Security and
                        Organization; detailed to assist the American representative on the United
                        Nations War Crimes Commission until April 1944.</note> act as alternate at
                    any meeting or part thereof. Detailed report follows.<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d819fn13">Not printed.</note> [Pell.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
